name: INSetProfileInCarIntentHandling
desc: The handler interface for restoring vehicle environment settings from a user-specified profile.DeprecatedThis intent is no longer available. You may define a custom intent instead. For more information, see Deprecated SiriKit Intent Domains.

items.name: func resolveProfileNumber(for: INSetProfileInCarIntent, with: (INIntegerResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the profile index from which to restore any settings.

items.name: func resolveProfileName(for: INSetProfileInCarIntent, with: (INStringResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the profile name from which to retrieve settings.

items.name: func resolveDefaultProfile(forSetProfileInCar: INSetProfileInCarIntent, with: (INBooleanResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves whether the profile can become the default profile.

items.name: func confirm(intent: INSetProfileInCarIntent, completion: (INSetProfileInCarIntentResponse) -> Void)
items.desc: Confirms whether you can restore the settings from the designated profile.

items.name: func handle(intent: INSetProfileInCarIntent, completion: (INSetProfileInCarIntentResponse) -> Void)
items.desc: Handles restoring settings from the designated profile.
